S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunication Identifier
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An identifier, such as words, numbers, letters, symbols, or any combination of those used to establish a contact to a particular person, organisation or service.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunication Carrier
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of a provider or type of carrier for a telecommunication service. This service may include land line based, shore based or satellite based radio connections.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Comment
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Comment regarding an entity obvious from context.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Other Data Type Description
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The description of other data type.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Location
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The location of a fragment of text or other information in a support file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of an entity of data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reported Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date that the item was observed, done, or investigated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Source
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The publication, document, or reference work from which information comes or is acquired.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: ISSN
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: International Standard Serial Number.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Character Encoding
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Encoding an element of a code set used for representing information.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Time of Day Start
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time corresponding to the start of an active period.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Time of Day End
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time corresponding to the end of an active period.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Day of Week is Range
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if the days of the week identified define a range or not.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Digital Signature Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: It means electronic signature value.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Digital Signature
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information in an electronic form attached to or logically combined with an electronic document to indicate that the signer has signed the electronic document.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dsa
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: American digital signature standards.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunication Services
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of methods of communication over a distance by electrical, electronic, or electromagnetic means.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: voice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The transfer or exchange of information by using sounds that are being made by mouth and throat when speaking.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: facsimile
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Sometimes called telecopying or telefax (the latter short for telefacsimile), is the telephonic transmission of scanned printed material (both text and images), normally to a telephone number connected to a printer or other output device.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sms
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Short Message Service is a form of text messaging communication on phones and mobile phones.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: data
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Materials that serve as the basis for initiation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: streamed data
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Data that is constantly received by and presented to an end-user while being delivered by a provider.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: telex
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system of communication in which messages are sent over long distances by using a telephone system and are printed by using a special machine (called a teletypewriter).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: telegraph
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An apparatus, system or process for communication at a distance by electric transmission over wire.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: email
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Messages and other data exchanged between individuals using computers in a network.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Support File Purpose
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Purpose of the file to be described in addition to the nautical product data.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: new
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: New support file purpose.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: replacement
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The act of furnishing an equivalent person or thing in the place of another.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: deletion
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Item in the process of being removed or deleted.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Support File Format
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: File format to describe in addition to nautical product data.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ASCII
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: American Standard Code for Information Interchange. American character standard code system established in 1968.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: JPEG2000
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Raster image compression technology based on wavelet transformation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: HTML
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Hypertext Markup Language. A type of basic web language used to create web documents.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: XML
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Extensible Markup Language. A language created by remarkably improving HTML to create Internet web pages.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: XSLT
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Extensible Stylesheet Language Transformations. XML-based language used to convert XML documents into other XML documents.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: VIDEO
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A digital recording of an image or set of images (such as a movie or animation).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: TIFF
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Tagged Image File Format.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: PDF/A or U/A
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: ISO-standardized version of the Portable Document Format (PDF) specialized for use in the archiving and long-term preservation of electronic documents or U/A.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: LUA
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A lightweight, extensible programming language.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: other
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Other support file purpose.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Authority
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The type of person, government agency or organisation granted powers of managing or controlling access to and/or activity in an area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: customs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The agency or establishment for collecting duties, tolls.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: border control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The administration to prevent or detect and prosecute violations of rules and regulations at international boundaries.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: police
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The department of government, or civil force, charged with maintaining public order.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: port
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Person or corporation, owners of, or entrusted with or invested with the power of managing a port. May be called a Harbour Board, Port Trust, Port Commission, Harbour Commission, Marine Department.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: immigration
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The authority controlling people entering a country.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: health
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The authority with responsibility for checking the validity of the health declaration of a vessel and for declaring free pratique.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: coast guard
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Organization keeping watch on shipping and coastal waters according to governmental law; normally the authority with responsibility for search and rescue.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: agricultural
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The authority with responsibility for preventing infection of the agriculture of a country and for the protection of the agricultural interests of a country.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: military
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A military authority which provides control of access to or approval for transit through designated areas or airspace.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: private company
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A private or publicly owned company or commercial enterprise which exercises control of facilities, for example a calibration area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: maritime police
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A governmental or military force with jurisdiction in territorial waters. Examples could include Gendarmerie Maritime, Carabinierie, and Guardia Civil.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: environmental
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An authority with responsibility for the protection of the environment.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fishery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An authority with responsibility for the control of fisheries.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: finance
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An authority with responsibility for the control and movement of money.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: maritime
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A national or regional authority charged with administration of maritime affairs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: hydrographic office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: State agency in charge of marine surveys.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RENC
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Regional ENC Coordination Centre Entities set up by the IHO.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: VARs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Value Added Resellers (VARs), who are able to offer comprehensive end-use services that bring together various navigational products into one package.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Day of Week
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Any one of seven days in a week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sunday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The first day of the week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: monday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The second day of the week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tuesday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The third day of the week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wednesday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The fourth day of the week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: thursday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The fifth day of the week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: friday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The sixth day of the week.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: saturday
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The last day of the week.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Organization Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of international organization in charge of nautical products.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Time Reference
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information about time reference.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: localTime
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The official time in a local region.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: UTC
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Greenwich Mean Time updated with leap seconds.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Comm Pref
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Category of preferred communication method.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: preferred calling
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The first choice channel or frequency to be used when calling a radio station.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: alternate calling
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A channel or frequency to be used for calling a radio station when the preferred channel or frequency is busy or is suffering from interference.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: preferred working
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The first choice channel or frequency to be used when working with a radio station.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: alternate working
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A channel or frequency to be used for working with a radio station when the preferred working channel or frequency is busy or is suffering from interference.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Schedule
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Kinds of operation method.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: normal operation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The service, office, is open, fully manned, and operating normally, or the area is accessible as usual.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: closure
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The service, office, or area is closed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: unmanned operation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The service is available but not manned.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Source Type
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Type of the source.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: law or regulation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Treaty, convention, or international agreement; law or regulation issued by a national or other authority.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: official publication
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Publication not having the force of law, issued by an international organisation or a national or local administration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mariner report, confirmed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Reported by mariner(s) and confirmed by another source.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mariner report, not confirmed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Reported by mariner(s) but not confirmed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: industry publications and reports
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Shipping and other industry publications, including graphics, charts and web sites.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: remotely sensed images
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Information obtained from satellite images.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: photographs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Information obtained from photographs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: products issued by HO service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Information obtained from products issued by Hydrographic Offices.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: news media
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Information obtained from news media.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: traffic data
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Information obtained from the analysis of traffic data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Administrative Division
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A generic term for an administrative region within a country at a level below that of the sovereign state.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Application Profile
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of an application profile that can be used with the online resource.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category Of Text
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of completeness of textual information in relation to the source material from which it is derived.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: abstract or summary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A statement summarizing the important points of a text.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: extract
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An excerpt or excerpts from a text.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: full text
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The whole text.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Chart Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Number of chart.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: City Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of a town or city.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Classification
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The act of distributing things into classes or categories of the same type.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Compilation Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The scale of something that is compiled.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Contact Instructions
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Instructions provided on how to contact a particular person, organisation or service.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Copyright
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A document granting exclusive right to publish and sell literary or musical or artistic work.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Country
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of a nation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Currency
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The metal or paper medium of exchange that is presently used.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Dataset Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A logical entity of data consisting of several elements (fields) grouped under one criterion.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The specified day of the month.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Delivery Point
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Details of where post can be delivered such as the apartment, name and/or number of a street, building or PO Box.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if a feature name is to be displayed in certain system display settings or not.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Where it is allowable to encode multiple instances of feature name for a single feature instance, only one feature name instance can indicate that the name is to be displayed (display name set to True).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Distribution Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Supply status of nautical products.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: production
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The act or process of producing something.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: withdrawn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The action to withdraw a time stamp (Used when a time stamp has been reported incorrectly).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Edition Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Edition date of the voyage product data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Edition Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Edition number of nautical product data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Locator
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The location of a fragment of text or other information in a support file.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Application schemas must describe how the associated file is identified. The associated file will commonly be named in a file reference co-attribute of the same complex attribute. Each DCEG must specify requirements for the format of the associated file and the semantics of file locator. For example, the value of file locator may be an HTML ID in an HTML file, line number in a text file) or a bookmark in a PDF file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Reference
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The file name of an externally referenced text file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Frame Dimension
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The magnitude of something in a particular direction of frame.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Headline
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Words set at the head of a passage or page to introduce or categorize.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Datum Reference
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Reference of geodetic points such as the longitude and latitude of the earth indicating horizontal position

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Individual Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of the person in charge.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: ISBN
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: International Standard Book Number.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: End Date

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Keyword
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The words that is used as a pattern to decode an encrypted message.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Language
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The method of human communication, either spoken or written, consisting of the use of words in a structured and conventional way.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Linkage
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Location (address) for on-line access using a URL/URI address or similar addressing scheme.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Main Panel
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Panel showing the default chart.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Marine Resource Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of marine resource.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Minimum Display Scale

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The individual name of a feature.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Nautical chart printed on paper.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ENC
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: All information related to the sailing of the ship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: raster nautical chart
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Raster information which is displayed visually.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: INT Chart
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A nautical chart with limits and scale in conformity with an internationally agreed scheme of such charts; carries the INT number of that sheet; conforms to the Chart Specifications of the IHO.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: nautical publication
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Used to relate additional nautical information or publications to the data.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: S-100 compliant product
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Data produced according to S-100-based product standards.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: electronic application for safety navigation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Electronic applications or products for safe navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: special purpose charts
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Nautical charts designed for special purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: e-Navigation service

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: others
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Other nautical products.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Protocol
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Connection protocol to be used. Example: ftp, http get KVP, http POST, etc.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Protocol Request
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Request used to access the resource. Structure and content depend on the protocol and standard used by the online resource, such as Web Feature Service standard.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Publication Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Publication number of the nautical product.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Purpose

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: new dataset
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Dataset having no previous example.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: new edition
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Edition having no previous example.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: update

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: re-issue

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cancellation

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Service Design

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Service Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Types of status of nautical services.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: provisional
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Under terms not final or fully worked out or agreed upon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: released
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Merchandise issued for sale or public showing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: deprecated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Data that is deprecated in importance and is no longer used and will disappear in the future.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: deleted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Item that has been removed or deleted.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Sounding Datum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Geodetic points for measuring the depth from the sea level to the sea floor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean low water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MLWS) - The average height of the low waters of spring tides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean lower low water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MLLWS) - The average height of lower low water springs at a place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean sea level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MSL) - The average height of the surface of the sea at a tide station for all stages of the tide over a 19-year period, usually determined from hourly height readings measured from a fixed predetermined reference level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lowest low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level conforming to the lowest tide observed at a place, or some what lower.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MLW) - The average height of all low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lowest low water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an arbitrary level conforming to the lowest water level observed at a place at spring tides during a period of time shorter than 19 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: approximate mean low water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within ' 0.3m from that of mean low water springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Indian spring low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (ISLW) - An arbitrary tidal datum approximating the level of the mean of the lower low water at spring tides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: low water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, approximating that of mean low water springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: approximate lowest astronomical tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within ' 0.3m from that of lowest astronomical tide (LAT).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: nearly lowest low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level approximating the lowest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the Indian spring low water (ISLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean lower low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MLLW) - The average height of the lower low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An approximation of mean low water adopted as the reference level for a limited area, irrespective of better determinations at a later date.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: approximate mean low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within ' 0.3m from that of mean low water (MLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: approximate mean lower low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within ' 0.3m from that of mean lower low water (MLLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean high water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MHW) - The average height of all high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean high water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MHWS) - The average height of the high waters of spring tides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: high water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest level reached at a place by the water surface in one tidal cycle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: approximate mean sea level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within ' 0.3m from that of mean sea level (MSL).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: high water springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, approximating that of mean high water springs (MHWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean higher high water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (MHHW) - The average height of higher high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: equinoctial spring low water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The level of low water springs near the time of an equinox.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lowest astronomical tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (LAT) - The lowest tide level which can be predicted to occur under average meterological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: local datum
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary datum defined by a local harbour authority, from which levels and tidal heights are measured by this authority.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: international great lakes datum 1985
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (IGLD 1985) - A vertical reference system with its zero based on the mean water level at Rimouski/Pointe-au-Pere, Quebec, over the period 1970 to 1988.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mean water level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of all hourly water levels over the available period of record.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lower low water large tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (LLWLT) - The average of the lowest low waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Higher High Water Large Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of the highest high waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: nearly highest high water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level approximating the highest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the high water springs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: highest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest tidal level which can be predicted to occur under average meteorological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: baltic Sea Chart Datum 2000
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (BSCD2000) - The datum refers to each Baltic country's realization of the European Vertical Reference System (EVRS) with land-uplift epoch 2000, which is connected to the Normaal Amsterdams Peil (NAP).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The production date of the source; for example the date of measurement.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: harbour

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A non-formatted digital text string.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Should be used, for example, to hold the information that is for short cautionary or explanatory notes. Therefore, text populated in text must not exceed 300 characters. Text may be in English, or in a national language. No formatting of text is possible within text. If formatted text, or text strings exceeding 300 characters, is required, then an alternate concept should be used.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ISO/IEC 8211
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Specification for a data descriptive file for information interchange.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: PDF
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Portable Document Format. A file format developed by Adobe in 1993 to present documents, including text formatting and images, in a manner independent of application software, hardware, and operating systems.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: HTML
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Hypertext Markup Language. A type of basic web language used to create web documents.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ePub
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: E-book file format.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: paper
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: For printing hydrographic charts, heavyweight, single layer paper is used. Such paper is generally made wholly or partly from rags and simulates hand-made paper. It is strong, moisture resistant and manufactured to withstand surface erasure.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: HDF-5
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Grid file format.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: other
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Other type of nautical product.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Datum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reference level used for expressing the vertical measurements of points on the earth's surface. Also called datum level, reference plane, levelling datum, datum for sounding reduction, datum for heights.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: When the vertical datum is unknown, such as water areas above locks, the value 'local datum' is to be used, and further details may be encoded using 'INFORM'. The +0.3m approximation quoted in the 'approximate' levels is somehow arbitrary and follows the British example of their definition for 'approximate LAT'.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Week

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Year
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A period of one revolution of the earth around the sun.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Time Intervals by Day of Week
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The regular weekly operation times of a service or schedule.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Support File Specification
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Specification of information on additional files used in addition to nautical products.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Schedule by Day of Week
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The nature and timings of a daily schedule by days of the week.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Default Locale
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Locale of an option that is selected automatically unless an alternative is specified.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Contact Address
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Direction or superscription of a letter, package, etc., specifying the name of the place to which it is directed, and optionally a contact person or organisation who should receive it.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Feature Name
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Provides the name of an entity, defines the national language of the name, and provides the option to display the name at various system display settings.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Graphic
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Pictorial information such as a photograph, sketch or other graphic, optionally accompanied by descriptive information about the graphic and the location relative to its subject from which it was made.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Information
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Textual information about the feature. The information may be provided as a string of text or as a file name of a single external text file that contains the text.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: At least one of the sub-attributes file reference or text must be populated.The sub-attribute file reference is generally used for long text strings or those that require formatting, however, there is no restriction on the type of text (except for lexical level) that can be held in files referenced by sub-attribute file reference.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Online Resource
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information about online sources from which a resource or data can be obtained.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Payment
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sum of money paid or a claim discharged.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Print Information
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information on the printing of nautical paper charts.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Product Specification
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Product standard name referenced when manufacturing nautical products.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Reference To NM
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Reference information of notice to mariners.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Service Specification
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Product standard name referenced when developing nautical product service.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Source Indication
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information about the source document, publication, or reference from which object data or textual material included or referenced in a dataset are derived.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Content of featureName is source authority name.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Support File
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information on additional files used in addition to nautical products.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunications
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Any transmission, emission, or reception of signs, signals, writing, images and sounds or intelligence of any nature by wire, radio, visual or other electromagnetic systems.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Text Content
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Textual material, or a pointer to a resource providing textual material. May be accompanied by basic information about its source and relationship to the source.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Exactly one of sub-attributes onlineResource or information must be completed in one instance of textContent. Product specifications may restrict the use or content of onlineResource for security. For example, a product specification may forbid populating onlineResource. Product specification authors must consider whether applications using the data product may be prevented from accessing off-system resources by security policies.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: The Authority

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: The Contact Details
